
    <!-- 1st About Us -->
    <section id="scroll">
        <div class="container px-5 about">
            <div class="row gx-5 align-items-center">
                <div class="col-lg-6 order-lg-2">
                   <div class="p-5"><%= image_tag("high-five.jpeg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Foster with dog") %>
                   </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-6 order-lg-1">
                    <div class="p-5">
                        <h2 class="display-4">About Us</h2>
                        <p>Compass Dog Rescue is dedicated to rescuing dogs from high kill shelters, specifically in the south, and guiding them North (hence the name - "Compass"). We do not have a facility, but work out of our homes. Dogs are kept in foster care until qualified, loving, forever homes can be found.</p>
                        <p>Compass tends to rescue dogs that are best suited for the northern climate. These breeds are generally long haired, shepherd purebreeds and mixes. However, we also accept other breeds, giving emphasis to personality. Our network continues to grow in the south Texas area, and we are not limited to assisting any specific city or town. </p>  
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    

