                            <h2 class="display-4">Meet The Fosters</h2>
                                <p>Our foster dogs are located out of state, awaiting transportation up north. Although most live in a home environment with their foster family for a few weeks, we have a few dogs in boarding due to a shortage of foster parents. We try not to rely on boarding, since we feel our dogs do better in a home life than at a boarding kennel.</p>
                                <p>Texas foster parents work together to transport dogs to doctor&apos;s appointments, provide information on training, and share other resources. They have different levels of experience fostering dogs over several years.</p>
                                <p>If you are interested in a dog, you can begin the process early, by submitting an applicataon while the dogs are still in foster care. No final decision will be made, until after the dogs arrive in Michigan. Please visit our Foster Dogs page to view dogs in our organization.</p> 
